<![CDATA[ <p>Yes, extensions. We are going to talk about extensions today. I know there are tons of articles that focus on extensions for the developers. But in this one, I will talk about the extensions I use and how these extensions help me daily for my productivity as a developer.</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/0*PbFMxd50qv7_Luu0" /><figcaption>Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@jstrippa?utm_source=medium&amp;utm_medium=referral">James Harrison</a> on <a href="https://unsplash.com?utm_source=medium&amp;utm_medium=referral">Unsplash</a></figcaption></figure><p>Let us start listing them</p><ol><li><strong>Vimium C</strong></li></ol><p>If you are a <a href="http://text_editor_of_superior_beings/">Vim</a> user then you probably know about this (assuming you use everything with vim keybinding). This add-on allows you to navigate/use a browser without using a mouse through keybinding and shortcuts.</p><figure><img alt="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*WwHneEH_WMyhcKLc_HMNHQ.png" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/proxy/1*WwHneEH_WMyhcKLc_HMNHQ.png" /></figure><p><em>Firefox add-on: </em><a href="https://mzl.la/3bciP1M"><em>https://mzl.la/3bciP1M</em></a><em>‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäGoogle extension: </em><a href="https://bit.ly/3zieKAR"><em>https://bit.ly/3zieKAR</em></a></p><p><strong>2. Bitwarden</strong></p><p>Who has ten different accounts for the same website just because the trial period lasts for only 15 days? And have hundreds of accounts across websites and apps? Well, I do, and I know most of you have. So, how do we remember those account credentials?‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäWe don‚Äôt. Bitwarden remembers them. Yeah, it‚Äôs a password manager.</p><figure><img alt="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*ZZhGtRnPIAS3vKAB1ugd5w.png" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/proxy/1*ZZhGtRnPIAS3vKAB1ugd5w.png" /></figure><p><em>Firefox add-on: </em><a href="https://mzl.la/3Q69qaA"><em>https://mzl.la/3Q69qaA</em></a><em>‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäGoogle extension: </em><a href="https://bit.ly/2IOyENd"><em>https://bit.ly/2IOyENd</em></a></p><p><strong>3. Temp Mail</strong></p><p>You just want to check out the website, but they want you to create an account? Well, Temp Mail will help you with disposable emails.</p><figure><img alt="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*3nsYTTdM21KcrcyNl2IAqw.png" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/proxy/1*3nsYTTdM21KcrcyNl2IAqw.png" /></figure><p>Firefox add-on: <a href="https://mzl.la/2QXzIRn">https://mzl.la/2QXzIRn</a>‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäGoogle Extension: <a href="https://bit.ly/3zIQl90">https://bit.ly/3zIQl90</a></p><p><strong>4. Octotree</strong></p><p>If you browse lots of open-source codes or spend significant time on GitHub looking at the different projects? Then this plugin might be a huge help for you. This plugin shows the GitHub repository in IDE like code tree, folder and files search, and many other cool features directly in your browser.</p><figure><img alt="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*Mou2eLJ_X4WdpkNQU8z3DQ.png" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/proxy/1*Mou2eLJ_X4WdpkNQU8z3DQ.png" /></figure><p>Firefox add-on: <a href="https://mzl.la/3zgI0Iw">https://mzl.la/3zgI0Iw</a>‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäGoogle Extension: <a href="https://bit.ly/3Q7z26Y">https://bit.ly/3Q7z26Y</a></p><p><strong>5. GitHub Repo Size</strong></p><p>Yeah, as the name says, it shows the size of a GitHub repository. It can be helpful before you go and clone a 1GB repository.</p><figure><img alt="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*6fe8RWrUcknTWMt4phj0Cw.png" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/proxy/1*6fe8RWrUcknTWMt4phj0Cw.png" /></figure><p>Firefox add-on: <a href="https://mzl.la/3zLzkeF">https://mzl.la/3zLzkeF</a>‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäGoogle Extension: <a href="https://bit.ly/3JhoOig">https://bit.ly/3JhoOig</a></p><p><strong>6. Tab Session Manager</strong></p><p>We all open tens of different browser tabs when we work on a project. And if we have to work on multiple projects, then the tens of tabs quickly become twenty more tabs. Tab Session Manager allows us to save groups of Tabs as a session so that we can organize and get back to them where we left off.</p><figure><img alt="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*5G4MuXBztbpdRg_0ftsJuA.png" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/proxy/1*5G4MuXBztbpdRg_0ftsJuA.png" /></figure><p>Firefox add-on: <a href="https://mzl.la/3cUarnN">https://mzl.la/3cUarnN</a>‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäGoogle Chrome Extension: <a href="https://bit.ly/3bf8ORc">https://bit.ly/3bf8ORc</a></p><p><strong>7. Imagus</strong></p><p>This plugin enlarges the thumbnails and shows images and videos from links with just a mouse hover. You don‚Äôt have to click and open it to see what is on another side of that link. Kinda cool right?</p><figure><img alt="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*koXFWybgsmLAwRiAmHljQQ.png" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/proxy/1*koXFWybgsmLAwRiAmHljQQ.png" /></figure><p>Firefox add-on: <a href="https://mzl.la/3cUarnN">https://mzl.la/3cUarnN</a>‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäGoogle Chrome Extension: <a href="https://bit.ly/3bf8ORc">https://bit.ly/3bf8ORc</a></p><p><strong>8. Dark Reader</strong></p><p>Don‚Äôt you just hate when you visit a website and it blasts the white light when you are working in a dark room? If you do the Dark Reader is your friend. It makes everything you see turn into a dark site (Kinda like magic).</p><figure><img alt="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*vECX4gtqZAY9DuhT5tYNUA.png" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/proxy/1*vECX4gtqZAY9DuhT5tYNUA.png" /></figure><p>Firefox add-on: <a href="https://mzl.la/3Q4CfnN">https://mzl.la/3Q4CfnN</a>‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäChrome extension: <a href="https://bit.ly/3SfmH2H">https://bit.ly/3SfmH2H</a></p><p><strong>9. Easy Screenshot</strong></p><p>This plugin enables us to take long screenshots of a website, not just the portion you see.</p><figure><img alt="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*ryo0MmP51iRisuqOtXcJuw.png" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/proxy/1*ryo0MmP51iRisuqOtXcJuw.png" /></figure><p>Firefox ad-on: <a href="https://mzl.la/3Bvmvq8">https://mzl.la/3Bvmvq8</a>‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäChrome extension: <a href="https://bit.ly/3vop3T6">https://bit.ly/3vop3T6</a> (exact same extension is not available in chrome since easy screenshot is made by Mozila)</p><p><strong>10. UBlock Origin</strong></p><p>I hate ads. And the solutions to that is uBlock Origin. This blocks trackers and ads from the websites.</p><figure><img alt="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*J5ylNMBhw_5m3khdcPxE9Q.png" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/proxy/1*J5ylNMBhw_5m3khdcPxE9Q.png" /></figure><p>Firefox ad-on: <a href="https://mzl.la/3zG2D26">https://mzl.la/3zG2D26</a>‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäChrome Extension: <a href="https://bit.ly/3JowfV2">https://bit.ly/3JowfV2</a></p><p><strong>11. Enhancer for Youtube</strong></p><p>This has many features but I like most is the mini video player on your side of the screen when you scroll through the comments.</p><figure><img alt="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*SH0dfr62DNFGDiMdwVxdag.png" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/proxy/1*SH0dfr62DNFGDiMdwVxdag.png" /></figure><p>Firefox ad-on: <a href="https://mzl.la/2AsjpTE">https://mzl.la/2AsjpTE</a>‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäChrome extension: <a href="https://bit.ly/2EGVpi4">https://bit.ly/2EGVpi4</a></p><p><strong>12. Grammarly</strong></p><p>Are you a native English speaker or like me whose English was a 4th language? Either way, Grammarly helps with your English and helps you send error-free (mostly) emails to your clients.</p><figure><img alt="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*4rIVqawomvkiCObHBaBU3A.png" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/proxy/1*4rIVqawomvkiCObHBaBU3A.png" /></figure><p>Firefox ad-on: <a href="https://mzl.la/3SfnwIP">https://mzl.la/3SfnwIP</a>‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäChrome extension: <a href="https://bit.ly/3zc6D8U">https://bit.ly/3zc6D8U</a></p><p><strong>13. SponsorBlock for Youtube</strong></p><p>This plugin skips the sponsor segments from YouTube videos. (Sorry, YouTubers).</p><figure><img alt="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/800/1*JD6zx1P_xHVUr72KwDSOzg.png" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/proxy/1*JD6zx1P_xHVUr72KwDSOzg.png" /></figure><p>Firefox ad-on: <a href="https://mzl.la/3zG5kRg">https://mzl.la/3zG5kRg</a>‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäChrome extension: <a href="https://bit.ly/3BuJG3I">https://bit.ly/3BuJG3I</a></p><p>That‚Äôs all for now. If there is anything else you use that has helped you then please do share with us.</p><img src="https://medium.com/_/stat?event=post.clientViewed&referrerSource=full_rss&postId=3c8c59c642e" width="1" height="1" alt=""><hr><p><a href="https://blog.devgenius.io/browser-add-on-extension-i-use-as-flutter-developer-3c8c59c642e">Browser add-on/extension I use as Flutter Developer.</a> was originally published in <a href="https://blog.devgenius.io">Dev Genius</a> on Medium, where people are continuing the conversation by highlighting and responding to this story.</p> ]]>
