<![CDATA[ <p>Enlarging on the Web Dev World, Extensions are a type of plugins or you can say they are software programs built on technologies such as <strong>HTML, CSS and JavaScript</strong>. These <strong>Software Programs are named Extensions</strong>; help users and <strong>developers to customize the chromes browsing experience.</strong></p><figure><img alt="Thumbnail for Article: Top Extensions for Web Developers." src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/1*eyI3lRgI9CtDt0wUshvZrA.png" /></figure><p>Today I‚Äôll introduce you with the list of <strong>Top 10 Extensions that a Web Developer</strong> can use.</p><p>Let‚Äôs Get started with the extensions‚Ää‚Äî‚Äästay tuned.</p><ol><li><strong>Lorem Ipsum Generator Tool:</strong></li></ol><p>It‚Äôs one of the best tool for web developers to give a stop to introducing pages while developing. As a Web Developer built web pages there are certain sections where the portion is to be left filled to determine the Design and User Experience. Here this tool will be very beneficial for them. This Tool will generate auto-text or filler-text for websites. Simply, Install this Plugin or Extension in your Chrome and set the range of characters and words of text you want to generate. This will auto-fill the area of text wherever it‚Äôs needed. Here‚Äôs <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/lorem-ipsum-generator-def/mcdcbjjoakogbcopinefncmkcamnfkdb">Link</a> to the Extension.</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/922/1*p-cHgPSOxvzrO1Dmc8mToA.png" /><figcaption><strong>Preview: </strong>Lorem Ipsum Generator Tool or Extension</figcaption></figure><p>2.<strong> CSS Viewer:</strong></p><p>It‚Äôs a simple tool for web developers, as it effectively works as the name implies itself. This Add-On tool displays the CSS Properties of a given page wherever you hover your mouse. Generally, A Small Popup Windows will appear showing you the data based on CSS that makes up the element you‚Äôre targeting on. This is a Hands-On tool to view the CSS Properties on a mouse hover. This Extensions have generated 100,000+ users with 4/5 for ease of use and simplicity. This Extension really has the medicine of again-and-again right clicking‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääinspect element and viewing CSS Properties. Here‚Äôs <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/cssviewer/ggfgijbpiheegefliciemofobhmofgce">Link</a> to the Extension.</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/946/1*8vV1LJzspB6cThf7c4Caxg.png" /><figcaption><strong>Preview: </strong>CSS Viewer Extension</figcaption></figure><p>3.<strong> HTML Validator:</strong></p><p>It‚Äôs a Reality Check tool for debugging your HTML Script within a browser. There are tons of HTML tools out there but this tools is outstanding. This Tool is Authentically useful for validating markup within a browser. Just Install the Extension, You need to open a developer window and navigate to HTML Validator Tab. All the Results will be displayed at the top with errors. This tool is quite popular and has a user list of 30,000+ users with 4/5 for usability. Here‚Äôs <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/html-validator/mpbelhhnfhfjnaehkcnnaknldmnocglk">Link</a> to the Extension.</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/943/1*LU3bCM0FNoe2Z9YpYXByKg.png" /><figcaption><strong>Preview: </strong>HTML Validator Extension</figcaption></figure><p>4. <strong>Githunt:</strong></p><p>Githunt is only and only useful if you devote lots of your time on GitHub looking for new projects to work-on. This tool will completely give you a green-check instead of wasting your time on GitHub‚Äôs Trending Page. This Add-On brings all the trending projects in a new tab at your browser to get a glance. Here you can search projects in various languages, also read a project description in brief with number of current open issues. Via this tool you can simply contribute to the new projects. Again, this tool has 4000+ users with 3/5 rating. Here‚Äôs <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/githunt/khpcnaokfebphakjgdgpinmglconplhp">Link</a> to the Extension.</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/961/1*LU2xr64LaXJZrp3Aj4xCXw.png" /><figcaption><strong>Preview: </strong>Githunt Extension</figcaption></figure><p>5. <strong>Keyframes:</strong></p><p>This Add-On is one of the best chrome extension for web developers who genuinely want to built CSS Animations within the browser. While there are thousands of tools out for animations, this extension outstands for creating short work of basic animations within a small popup window. Just Install Keyframes, Open the Web-Page, Select the Red and Blue Icon and Highlight a CSS element you want to animate. Edit that element in the side box to add your won piece of animation to the page. It‚Äôs Marked as Simple and Smart Work. This Tool has 20,000+ users with rating of 3.6/5 for being authentic. <strong>Currently, this Extension is Not Available but be tuned and keep checking</strong>; Here‚Äôs <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/keyframes/dalaiblmpeklkjnpeocmaojcfldmbfck">Link</a> to the Extension.</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1024/1*IUyBhSOaTDLY_lAjaNixnQ.jpeg" /><figcaption><strong>Preview: </strong>Keyframe Extension</figcaption></figure><p>6. <strong>BrowserStack:</strong></p><p>Really, this tools stand out exceptionally useful as a chrome add-on or extension for web developers. This Tool allows you to test your work on different types of browsers and to check responsiveness of the web-page or apps. Install the Extension, Open the Web-Page in Chrome and Select BrowserStack and select the device option from the tab. Then your Web-Page will start rendering using an emulator of a browser on that device. It‚Äôs a Simple but very Effective tool. Here‚Äôs <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/browserstack/nkihdmlheodkdfojglpcjjmioefjahjb">Link</a> to the Extension.</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/909/1*FxIoGbm3t6q6RZnm7ame8Q.png" /><figcaption><strong>Preview: </strong>BrowserStack Extension</figcaption></figure><p>7.<strong> ColorPick Eyedropper:</strong></p><p>This tool is a detailed color selector for web-pages. It‚Äôs a Effective Chrome Developer Extension due to it‚Äôs high efficiency in resulting out detailed color code and names. This Tool cannot be used everyday but ranges as a hands-on tool for developers. Once you install this Add-On, you simply select the colour wheel icon to activate it. Your Cursor will change to a crosshair, highlight the section you want to make results and you‚Äôll immediately see the RGB values and hex appears on right side of the screen. Here‚Äôs <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/colorpick-eyedropper/ohcpnigalekghcmgcdcenkpelffpdolg">Link</a> to the Extension.</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/925/1*yakYhKjUouf8Fu5lvnA9Kw.png" /><figcaption><strong>Preview: </strong>ColorPicker Eyedropper Extension</figcaption></figure><p>8. <strong>Window Resizer:</strong></p><p>As I earlier introduced to the tool called ‚ÄúBrowserStack‚Äù, this work exact as that tool. Windows Resizer is useful chrome extension for web developers. It‚Äôs help with working with responsive design of apps and websites. After Installation of this tool, it will show you option to resize the screen you‚Äôre working on a range of screen sizes, and like this you can check the responsiveness of your app for website. Here‚Äôs <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/window-resizer/kkelicaakdanhinjdeammmilcgefonfh/">Link</a> to the Extension.</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/928/1*DRS8WQVm-8lFkp3u3UG_uw.png" /><figcaption><strong>Preview: </strong>Windows Resizer Extension</figcaption></figure><p>9. <strong>Corporate Ipsum:</strong></p><p>It‚Äôs an alternative to Lorem Ipsum Generator. If your client or customer is more picky about the placeholder text, you can easily use this tool to generate Lorem Ipsum with Corporate style. The Text will be unique and will have a corporate twist. This tool has 10,000+ users with 4/5 for ease of use. Here‚Äôs <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/corporate-ipsum/lfmadckmfehehmdnmhaebniooenedcbb">Link</a> to the Extension.</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/973/1*OwoKzISoevlOEkAPmTO5Hg.png" /><figcaption><strong>Preview: </strong>Corporate Ipsum Extension</figcaption></figure><p>10. <strong>Fonts Ninja:</strong></p><p>It actually identifies the font on web-page. After Installation of this Add-On you should see a small green ninja icon in your toolbar. Open your Chrome Browser, Select the Icon and hover a font which you want to identify. After, you‚Äôll see a overview popup and an individual popup over the highlighted font. Here‚Äôs <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/fonts-ninja/eljapbgkmlngdpckoiiibecpemleclhh">Link</a> to the Extension.</p><figure><img alt="" src="https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/921/1*LFwBEqx10hgqK2D_KLwKGQ.png" /><figcaption><strong>Preview: </strong>Fonts Ninja Extension</figcaption></figure><p>So, this was an article on Top 10 Extensions for Web Developers.</p><p><strong>Note: </strong>This Article do not promote any kind of service or extension. It‚Äôs Only for Educational Purpose.</p><p><strong>Update:</strong> (09/02/2022)‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäExtension 5: Keyframes is not currently available on Chrome Store, the reason is unknown for me. I will soon update this article with the alternative of this add-on. <em>After Unavailability, The Reason I have mentioned this extension is the Ease of Use. If the Extension is Live Again you can get it or soon I&#39;ll replace that extension with an alternative.</em></p><p>Stay Tuned and Follow me on Medium‚Ää‚Äî‚Ää<a href="https://medium.com/u/d4942c3fdf94">Harshal Suryawanshi</a>. Also don‚Äôt forget to <strong>comment</strong> your favorite extension and experiences below. <strong>Share </strong>this article.</p><img src="https://medium.com/_/stat?event=post.clientViewed&referrerSource=full_rss&postId=d57b483b99f2" width="1" height="1" alt=""><hr><p><a href="https://blog.devgenius.io/top-10-extensions-for-web-developers-d57b483b99f2">Top 10 Extensions for Web Developers</a> was originally published in <a href="https://blog.devgenius.io">Dev Genius</a> on Medium, where people are continuing the conversation by highlighting and responding to this story.</p> ]]>
